text: Jones County is a county in the state of Texas in the United States. In 2020, 19,663 people lived there. The county seat is Anson. It was named for Anson Jones, the fifth president of the Republic of Texas. Alcoholic drinks can not be purchased in Jones County. == Geography == The county has a total area of 937 square miles. == References == Category:Texas counties
title: Jones County, Texas
